## 2. Core API Conventions

### Router structure
- Routers in `core/api/`; prefix/tags in `core/main.py`
- Use `Depends(get_tenant)`; `assert_agent_allowed(tenant, agent)` when route accepts agent name
- Pydantic models colocated in route files (see `events.py`, `memory.py`)

### Event write — always use shared service
```python
from services.event_write import write_event

return await write_event(
    tenant_id=tenant["tenant_id"],
    agent=body.agent,
    event=body.event,
    data=body.data,
    parent_id=body.parent_id,
    session_id=body.session_id,
    metadata=body.metadata,
)
```

### Search / memory
- Embedding: `await generate_embedding(text, tenant_id)` from `services/embeddings.py`
- Qdrant filter MUST include `tenant_id`; add `agent_id` when scoped
- Hydrate full events from Postgres after Qdrant returns IDs

### Qdrant
- Collection: `agent_events` (`QDRANT_COLLECTION` in `connection.py`)
- Point ID = string `event_id` UUID
- Payload: `tenant_id`, `agent_id`, `event_type`, `timestamp`
- On delete (forget, agent delete): remove from Postgres AND Qdrant

### Auth edge cases
- `looks_like_jwt()` — 3 dot segments; API keys must not be treated as JWT
- Admin routes under `/v1/admin` return 404 (not 403) for unauthorized

### Error responses
- 401 invalid/revoked key
- 403 agent-scoped key mismatch
- 400 embedding not configured (search/context)

### Do not
- Duplicate event INSERT outside `event_write.py`
- Skip `tenant_id` filter on events/agents queries
- Use default JWT secrets in production configs

