## 3. SDK, MCP & Integrations

### Integration paths (same backend)
| Path | Install | Best for |
|------|---------|----------|
| Python SDK | `pip install zizkadb-sdk` | FastAPI agents, notebooks |
| TypeScript SDK | `npm install zizkadb-sdk` | Node, Bun, Deno |
| MCP | `uvx zizkadb-mcp` | Cursor, Claude Desktop — no app code changes |
| REST | curl / any HTTP | Go, Rust, Java, mobile |

Cloud: `ZizkaDB("zizkadb_live_xxxx")`. Self-host: `ZizkaDB(host="http://localhost:8000")`.

### SDK parity (required)
When adding/changing a public method, update BOTH:
- `sdk/python/zizkadb/client.py` — snake_case params
- `sdk/typescript/src/index.ts` — camelCase options

Models: `sdk/python/zizkadb/models.py`, `sdk/typescript/src/types.ts`

### Naming map
| Python | TypeScript | REST wire |
|--------|------------|-----------|
| `parent_id` | `parentId` | `parent_id` |
| `session_id` | `sessionId` | `session_id` |
| `event_id` | `eventId` | `event_id` |
| `context_for()` | `contextFor()` | POST `/v1/memory/context` |
| `memory_diff()` | `memoryDiff()` | GET `/v1/memory/diff/{id}` |
| `context_for_full()` | `contextForFull()` | same endpoint, full response |
| `query()` | `query()` | GET `/v1/events` |
| `baseline()` | `baseline()` | GET `/v1/agents/{id}/baseline` |
| `agents()` | `agents()` | GET `/v1/agents` |
| `why()` | `why()` | GET `/v1/events/{id}/why` |
| `search()` | `search()` | POST `/v1/search` |
| `at()` | `at()` | GET `/v1/events/at` |
| `forget()` | `forget()` | DELETE `/v1/memory/forget` |

### Error mapping
| HTTP | Python | TypeScript |
|------|--------|------------|
| 401 | `AuthError` | `AuthError` |
| 403 | `AgentScopeError` | `AgentScopeError` |
| 404 | `NotFoundError` | `NotFoundError` |
| 429 | `RateLimitError` | `ZizkaDBError` |

### Client defaults
- Cloud: `https://db.zizka.ai`
- Local: auto-inject `zizkadb_dev_local` or `DEV_API_KEY`
- Env: `ZIZKADB_API_KEY` (preferred), legacy `AGENTDB_API_KEY`
- Telemetry opt-out: `ZIZKADB_TELEMETRY=false`

### MCP (`mcp/zizkadb_mcp/server.py`)
- Each tool maps 1:1 to REST via `_api(method, path, body)`
- Env: `ZIZKADB_HOST`, `ZIZKADB_API_KEY` (legacy `AGENTDB_*` aliases work)
- MIT license — no AGPL core imports in MCP
- Template: `.cursor/mcp.json.example`

| MCP tool | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `log_event` | Log with optional causal parent |
| `search_memory` | Semantic search |
| `get_context` | Prompt-ready memory block |
| `why` | Causal chain |
| `query_events` | List/filter events |
| `time_travel` | State at timestamp |
| `memory_diff` | Session summary |
| `forget` | GDPR delete by data filter |

### LangChain (`integrations/langchain/`)
- `ZizkaDBCallbackHandler` — LangChain run tree → `parent_id` via `_run_parents`
- Events: `llm_start`, `llm_end`, `tool_start`, `tool_end`, `chain_error`

### CrewAI (`integrations/crewai/`)
- Manual: `ZizkaDBCrewLogger` — `log_kickoff`, `log_task`, `log_output`

### Integration pattern
1. `log()` every decision with `parent_id` chain
2. `session_id` per conversation (required for baselines)
3. `context_for()` before LLM turn
4. `why(event_id)` on failures — pass event_id, not agent name

