## 6. Add API Endpoint

### Workflow
1. Choose router in `core/api/` or create + register in `core/main.py`
2. Pydantic models; `Depends(get_tenant)`; `assert_agent_allowed` if agent param
3. Reuse `write_event`, `generate_embedding`, `get_pool()`, `get_qdrant()`
4. SDK parity + MCP + tests + docs

### Checklist
```
- [ ] Pydantic models in core/api/<area>.py
- [ ] Depends(get_tenant) + assert_agent_allowed where needed
- [ ] tenant_id in every SQL WHERE clause
- [ ] Reuse write_event — no duplicate INSERT
- [ ] Register router in core/main.py if new file
- [ ] OpenAPI valid at /swagger
- [ ] Python SDK + TypeScript SDK updated
- [ ] MCP tool if user-facing
- [ ] wiki/REST-API.md + dashboard/app/docs/sections.tsx
- [ ] Integration test in core/tests/
```

### POST template
```python
@router.post("", status_code=201)
async def my_endpoint(body: MyRequest, tenant: dict = Depends(get_tenant)):
    assert_agent_allowed(tenant, body.agent)
    return await write_event(tenant_id=tenant["tenant_id"], ...)
```

